cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to predict subsequent events in a narrative. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a graph neural network to model event interactions, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a knowledge base and inference techniques, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval from a large corpus of news articles, which could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for script event prediction, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
